			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>But i case of Windows or macOS (and Android too), user rarely has to operate via command line. On Linux this is not optional, it&#8217;s mandatory. It&#8217;s all about user experience. The only times I have to resort to command line or text file editing is when I&#8217;m dealing with open source tools that either originate from Linux or were developed on it, or with Python. Text file edits are reserved for some games, when developers didn&#8217;t include a way to scale up the graphics&#8230;</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->
			<div class="report-abuse">
                
			<span id="safe-comments-result-6362390"><a class="hide-if-no-js" href="javascript:void(0);" onclick="return confirm('Are you sure you want to report this comment?')?safe_report_comments_flag_comment( '6362390', '6cc2f59227', 'safe-comments-result-6362390'):'';">Report comment</a></span>            </div>
