				<p>I agree it is overused in some situations, for example if you get sent a form you need to sign and email back but it&#8217;s a pdf and you can&#8217;t edit it or from worksheets or cover sheets at Uni. </p>
<p>PDFs should only be used for final copies of documents to be sent or put on a website like data sheets or read only documents or documents that need password protected.</p>
