			<div class="comment-content">
				<p>I had to generate PDF invoices.  HTML2PDF tools produced sub-optimal output.  I found &#8220;prawn&#8221; surprisingly easy to use and an elegant way to learn the structure of PDF.  I have full control over the output.  I went from hating PDF to enjoying it.</p>
<p>Only peripherally related, I like eps2svg (from the &#8220;geg&#8221; package) to take PostScript output such as gEDA schematics and produce SVG files for resolution-independent consumption on the web.</p>
			</div><!-- .comment-content -->
